{"_id":"1NCxDczhirh2RU1b","name":"Overseer","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: The Sanctioned Psyker's Comrade keeps him in check, but he also keeps him protected. If given this Command, the Comrade steps forward, protecting the Sanctioned Psyker from any incoming attacks. For the next Round, as long as the Comrade is in Cohesion, he is struck with any attacks that would have normally hit the Psyker. However, if the Weapon Skill or Ballistic Skill Test on the Attack result was a double, the Attack hits the Psyker, and is resolved as a normal hit.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"overseer","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"psyker","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"1vNAbQ2OsTTCGKkP","name":"Wary of Outsiders","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Death worlders tend to be slow to put their faith in anyone other than themselves and their comrades, and they chafe at the expectations and strictures of more civilised society. They suffer a -10 penalty on all Interaction Skill Tests made in formal surroundings, and similarly impose a -10 penalty on any Interaction Skill Tests made on them by any non-death worlders. These penalties can be waived at the GM's discretion if the death worlders are dealing with those who have earned their trust.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"waryofoutsiders","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"deathworld","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"But It Dark in Dere!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Despite their fearsome and fearless nature, Ogryns are extremely claustrophobic. They will not enter caves, basements, ruins, infantry fighting vehicles like the Chimera, or even smaller than average buildings, of their own free will. Officers and Commissars can order them into such places, but suffer a -10 penalty to any Command Skill Tests to do so, and Ogryns suffer a -10 to all Skill Tests when so confined.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"bidid","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"ogryn","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4l64Ptt6XxTR9XVk"}
{"_id":"6B4ZxxIQcbtXjcgz","name":"Loader","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: As long as his Comrade is in Cohesion, the Heavy Gunner may use his Comrade's Actions to reload his currently equipped weapon. These may be used in combination with the Heavy Gunner's Actions. For example, to reload a gun that requires a Full Action to reload, the Heavy Gunner spends a Half Action Reload, and his Comrade performs a Half Action Reload, reloading the gun and leaving them both with a Half Action remaining.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"loader","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"heavy","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"7f0wiVQJv3NLEZ6R","name":"Curate","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: Whenever the Ministorum Priest triggers Righteous Fury on a Melee Attack, and his Comrade is in Cohesion, his Comrade may grant a temporary Fate Point to any Player Character within communications range. This temporary Fate Point may be spent as normal (see page 33), but may not be burnt. If the temporary Fate Point has not been spent by the end of the encounter, it is lost.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"curate","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"priest","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9vQNAKhsbG8h3JMC","name":"Set-Up Shot","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: The Ratling's Comrade fires off a shot that distracts the Ratling's target from the real threat. The Ratling's next Ranged Attack cannot be Dodged. The Ratling's Comrade must be in Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"setupshot","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"ratling","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Doy5DFBzfZ24hcvx","name":"Untempered Zeal","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The pious spirit of the penitent is almost unmatched in its ferocity, and while their faith is closer to the violent ardour of the fanatic than the divine clarity of the Adepta Sororitas, it is nonetheless inspiring to behold. Penitent characters may re-roll any failed Charm Test to inspire religious fervour or righteous hatred in others.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"untemperedzeal","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"penitent","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"F9aFY8soOIGiJP6i","name":"Spotter","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Ratling's Comrade carries magnoculars and other tools to help line up the perfect sniper shot. If the Ratling is using an Accurate weapon, and his Comrade is in Cohesion, the Ratling may use his Comrade to make an Aim Action, and gain the benefits himself.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"spotter","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"ratling","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Duty and Honour","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The highborn hold themselves to standards of behaviour and etiquette, their upbringing distinguishing them from the low-born troopers that make up the common bulk of the Imperial Guard. Highborn characters suffer a -10 penalty on all Charm, Inquiry, and Deceive Tests made to interact with characters who are not highborn. However, they gain a +10 bonus on all those same Skill Tests when dealing with the nobility and other high authority in formal situations.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"dutyandhonour","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"highborn","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FdwAG9HLy61sRkxX"}
{"_id":"GUQoqav04aC5DvFf","name":"Armsman","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Weapons Specialist is a master in the use of many weapons, and often needs different ones for different situations. His Comrade carries all of the necessary weapons with him, keeping them ready for the Weapons Specialist when the time comes. As long as his Comrade is in Cohesion, the Weapon Specialist may switch to any of his weapons as a Free Action.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"armsman","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"weaponspec","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Augmentics","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The regiment gains an additional +10 on all Logistics Tests made to obtain bionic replacements and implants.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"augmentics","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"doctrine, tech","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JTn4qhbpDkql9rEw"}
{"_id":"L5RgNcTe2SFggORh","name":"Vox-Tech","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Sergeant is accompanied by a Vox-Tech who can relay orders out to his men over the din of battle. As long as his Comrade is in Cohesion with him, all of the Sergeant's orders affect all Comrades within vox range.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"voxtech","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"sergeant","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MdUyyYcQJ21mIawm","name":"Stabilise","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: The Heavy Gunner's Comrade helps brace the weapon for firing, keeping the recoil from throwing off the Heavy Gunner's aim. Any Semi-Auto Burst or Full-Auto Burst Actions used by the Heavy Gunner this Turn are made with a +10 modifier to the Ballistic Skill Test instead of the modifier normally bestowed by the Action. This Order can only be issued to the Comrade if he is in Cohesion with the Player Character.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"stabilise","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"heavy","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NpK3hflCufF9agqK","name":"Get Them!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Sweeping Order (Free Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: As part of this order, the Sergeant must make a Challenging (+0) Command Test. If he succeeds, all Comrades in communications range become inspired by the Sergeant's fervour, charging into battle with a renewed zeal. For the next Round, when performing the Ranged Volley or Close Quarters Orders, the Comrades grant their controlling Player Character an additional +4 Damage to the affected Melee or Ranged Attack.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"getthem","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"sergeant","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"OBaAveX46DV1pmFN","name":"Fierce Loyalty","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: Ogryns become very attached to those around them, and can gain strong connections to their Comrades. If the Ogryn's Comrade is not in Cohesion with the Ogryn, or is within 10 metres of another Player Character and engaged in melee with an enemy, the Ogryn becomes Frenzied (see page 144) and gains an additional +10 Strength and +10 Toughness until his Comrade is either safe or dead. If the Comrade dies, the Ogryn becomes inconsolable for hours.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"fierceloyalty","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"ogryn","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Blessed Ignorance","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Imperial citizens know that the proper ways of living are those tried and tested by the generations that have gone before. Horror, pain, and death are the just rewards of curiosity, for those that look too deeply into the mysteries of the universe are all too likely to find malefic beings looking back at them. Their wise blindness imposes a -5 penalty on all Forbidden Lore (Int) Tests.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"blessedignorance","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"imperial","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OIcY7YsLZ8VqHP63"}
{"_id":"OSnlUkbE215kGidQ","name":"Field Repairs","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: On the battlefield, the Enginseer links to his Servitor, relaying complex data and instructions, and the Servitor enacts those commands with precision. As long as his Servitor is within range of communication, the Enginseer may perform Tech-Use Tests on anything next to the Servitor at a -10 penalty.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"fieldrepairs","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"techpriest","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"SgK30w0XOY9i2dIp","name":"Righteous Oration","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: The Ministorum Priest's Comrade forcefully recites litanies, inspiring all those who can hear him. All Player Characters within communications range may re-roll all Damage rolls for the next Round. The Comrade pours so much fervour and energy into his Oration that afterwards, he is exhausted, and may not use Righteous Oration again for the duration of the encounter.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"righteousoration","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"priest","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"VSVQ9tiOTxYpy3hP","name":"Demolitions","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The regiment gains a +10 bonus on all Logistics Tests made to obtain grenades, missiles, explosives, and special tank ammunition.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"demolitions","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"doctrine","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Y78xuATVpIsr5x8C","name":"Protector","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Storm Trooper keeps a watchful eye on the less trained members of his Squad, keeping them safe with his superior training. Whenever any Comrade within 10 metres of the Storm Trooper would take a hit that would kill him, the Storm Trooper may take the hit instead, rolling Damage as normal.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"protector","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"stormtrooper","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YoMS4yjK87fjZgDh","name":"Hail of Fire","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: With just a look, the Weapon Specialist signals his Comrade to lay down a coordinated hail of fire. If the Weapon Specialist's Comrade is in Cohesion, all of the targets of the Weapon Specialist's attacks this Turn must take a Challenging (+0) Pinning Test or become Pinned (see Pinning on page 254).</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"hailoffire","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"weaponspec","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZT7KXtUakiWKXqnx","name":"Larcenous","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Hailing from worlds where the black market is the only market, penal colonists are skilled at obtaining illicit items, whether to sell, on or for their own purposes. Penal colony characters add a +10 to all Logistics Tests made to acquire illegal or contraband items.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"larcenous","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"penal","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Bred for War","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Fortress worlders possess an entirely justified siege mentality, a natural result of daily lives shaped by the need for perpetual vigilance against an enemy that could strike at any time, and the discipline required to respond to that threat swiftly and effectively. Fortress worlders are loyal almost to a fault, and reluctant to disobey orders even with good reason, lacking personal initiative, and becoming inflexible as a result. A fortress worlder must attempt a Challenging (+0) Willpower Test in order to go against the rules and regulations of the Imperial Guard.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"bredforwar","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"fortress","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZeLiGK307iwn3Duk"}
{"_id":"aECiaiygjj3eCgRE","name":"Gunner","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: When the Operator is driving a multi-passenger vehicle, his Comrade can jump in and man one of the guns, firing upon the Operator's command. If the Operator spends his Turn driving a vehicle, he may also make a Ranged Attack Action using whatever gun his Comrade is manning, as if he were stationed at it himself. This uses the Comrade's Full Action for the Turn.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"gunner","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"operator","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Survivalists","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"When selecting this doctrine, nominate a single type of terrain&mdash;Desert, Jungle, Tundra, Ash Wastes, Urban Ruins, etc. When operating in that kind of terrain, characters from a regiment with this Doctrine can re-roll failed Survival and Navigate (Surface) Skill Tests.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"Desert, Jungle, Tundra, Ash Wastes, Urban Ruins,  etc.","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"survavlists","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"training","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aLfKL9jlqGk5R8G3"}
{"name":"Scavengers","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The regiment may choose to gain a +10 bonus on any Logistics Test. However, on any test where this bonus is used, if any doubles are rolled (22, 33, 44, etc.) whether the Test was a success or a failure, then the scavenging and stealing attracts unwanted attention from higher authorities within the Imperial Guard or the Departmento Munitorum.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"scavengers","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"doctrine, logistics","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dnKdAPeTAJyKf37Z"}
{"_id":"fy2qLAOWEaAxnpSv","name":"Covering Fire","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Sweeping Order (Free Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: All Comrades in communications range fire wildly at the enemy, keeping them pinned down and protecting their fellows from retaliation. For the next Round, all Player Characters with their Comrade in Cohesion gain a +10 to all Dodge Tests.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"coveringfire","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"sergeant","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hppGPWjZJE4hdCXq","name":"Snap Out of It!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Sweeping Order (Free Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: As part of this order, the Sergeant must make a Challenging (+0) Intimidate or Command Test. If he succeeds, all Comrades in communication range end any ongoing Fear or Pinning effects. They may act normally in subsequent Turns.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"snapoutofit","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"sergeant","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"iU3oBTxqwhydDDDU","name":"Mentor","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Full Action</p>\n<p>Effect: The Storm Trooper has undergone extensive training in the Schola Progenium, and can often pass on small tricks to help the rest of the Squad thrive in the battlefield. Once per game session, the Storm Trooper may impart his training to his Squad. All Squad members in communications range (including Player Characters) may take all Skill Tests in a single Skill of the Storm Trooper's choosing as if they had the Storm Trooper's Skill Training. Once activated, this effect lasts until the end of the encounter, or ten minutes in narrative time.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"mentor","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"stormtrooper","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kpE0w5udL0s0Ap2C","name":"Put that Out!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: If the Operator's vehicle catches fire, the Operator's Comrade jumps into action. If the Comrade is inside the affected vehicle, he spends a Full Action to end any Fire effect currently afflicting the vehicle.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"putthatout","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"operator","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"m5GIwLQPy8a73mF1","name":"Little 'un","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: Those Guardsmen that choose to tolerate the presence of the Ogryn tend to be the ones of similar build. However, even the largest Guardsman is tiny in the eyes of an Ogryn, and gain the affectionate name &ldquo;little &lsquo;uns.&rdquo; The Ogryn's Comrade gains an extra Wound State. He can now be either Healthy, Lightly Wounded, Heavily Wounded, or Dead.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"littleun","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"ogryn","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"pfO7gEW3TTQ9Ikbt","name":"Servo-Arm","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Servitor assists in all repairs the Enginseer performs, acting as a natural extension of his will as he communes with vehicle machine spirits. When assisted by his Servitor, the Enginseer gains a +10 bonus to all Tech-Use Tests to make repairs, and halves the time any repair takes.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"servoarm","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"techpriest","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"qXm9FDw88zBfTPob","name":"Medicae Auxilia","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Comrade assists the Medic in treating his patients, quickly responding to any situation that arises. For Extended Care Medicae Tests, the Medic's Comrade counts as an assistant trained in Medicae. Additionally, the Medic's Medicae Test suffers no penalty for additional patients.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"medicaeauxilia","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"medic","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Clumsy","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Ogryn's hands are not only much larger than those of a normal human, but also far stronger, and most Ogryn have a hard time using them to perform delicate, or even normal, tasks. Because of this, Ogryn cannot use most weapons made for humans, as they tend to break them when they try. Any weapon which doesn't have the Ogryn-Proof Trait cannot be used by a character with the Clumsy Trait.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"clumsy","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"ogryn","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rxRHx8fPOd5k68u5"}
{"_id":"tYA9iAq2NSinAXiX","name":"Ultimate Sanction","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Psyker's Comrade carefully watches him for any signs that he might be losing control of his powers, ready to step in with any means necessary. As long as his Comrade is in Cohesion, the Sanctioned Psyker may take 1d5 Wounds, ignoring Armour and Toughness, to re-roll any result on Table 7-2: Psychic Phenomena (see page 227).</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"ultimatesanction","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"psyker","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"u0qvwCHMm0rF6yiI","name":"Only One Life to Give","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"So driven to martyrdom are the penitent, that it can drive them to take unnecessary risks, lamenting that they can only sacrifice themselves once. Penitent characters must pass an Ordinary (+10) Willpower Test in order to retreat from combat or otherwise act in the interests of self-preservation.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"ooltg","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"penitent","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Hivebound","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Hive worlders seldom endure the horrors of the open sky or suffer the indignities of the great outdoors. Whilst outside of an enclosed or artificial environment (such as a hive city, starship or similar), they suffer a -10 penalty to all Survival Tests, due to their continued unfamiliarity with such places.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"hivebound","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"hiveworld","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"unMibSh7qmr8ubcP"}
{"_id":"vEk3nHMyTXMZvCt5","name":"Field Treatment","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: The Comrade acts as a natural extension of the Medic on the battlefield. The Medic relays him complex medical instructions, and the Comrade obeys with precision. As long as his Comrade is within range of communication, the Medic may perform Medicae Tests on any character next to the Comrade at a -10 penalty.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"fieldtreatment","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"medic","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Acustomed to Crowds","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Hive worlders grow up surrounded by crowds, and they are used to weaving through even the densest mobs with ease. Crowds do not count as Difficult Terrain for hive worlders, and when Running or Charging through a dense crowd, hive worlders take no penalty to Agility Tests to keep their feet.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"acustomedtocrowds","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"hiveworld","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vHywn8ruqKZEGcva"}
{"name":"Galvanising Presence","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The members of the Squad feel the Commissar&rsquo;s watchful eye upon them, keeping them in line with his strict justice. When employing the Terrify special use of the Command Skill, its effects apply to all members of his Squad, including Player Characters. Additionally, the Commissar counts as having Fear (2) for the purpose of all Terrify Tests.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"galvanisingpresence","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"commissar","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZVWYA4xDuaE7bJDN"}
{"name":"Summary Execution","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Half Action</p>\n<p>Effect: The Commissar begins to see his men falter before their enemy, and must use his Bolt Pistol to reinforce the reason they fight. If a Player Character within range of the Commissar falls below 0 Wounds, the Commissar may perform a Summary Execution on that character&rsquo;s Comrade. The Commissar makes a Challenging (+0) Ballistics Skill Test to fire on the Comrade. If he succeeds, he kills the Comrade, and properly motivates the Player Character to fight on. The Player Character ignores all Critical Effects until the end of combat, and regains 1d5 Wounds as he finds a new resolve.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"summaryexecution","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"commissar","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"W69W8FypW8KwFF0D"}
